Markets will do what markets do, Johnny. I am basically just referencing a bogus "deal" in substance/context. Enjoy the weekend.

@realmoney The Art of the Farce The China trade deal is a joke. Its an agricultural purchase deal without text, contract and foundation. It is not even being disguised as anything other than an ag deal. It is the same deal that has been in play for months. China knows it,

economists know it but investors don't - there is no change in structural reform (tech transfer, IP theft, currency, etc.). The US is not even pretending now and China is not even commenting. My bet is that even this superficial deal has a chance of breaking down in 2020.

Phase Two? Give me a break - it was "dead at birth." Enjoy the day and the weekend. @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @jimcramer @tomkeene @business @realdonaldtrump @michaelsantoli @carlquintanilla @lizclaman
